  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is Google's internal code review policy/process?",
  "response": "Google has a well-established code review policy and process that is integral to its software development practices. While specific details might evolve over time and may not be publicly available in their entirety, the general principles and practices typically include:\n\n1. **Importance of Code Reviews**: Code reviews at Google are seen as a vital part of the development process. They help ensure code quality, encourage knowledge sharing, and promote collaboration among team members.\n\n2. **Peer Review**: All code changes generally require a peer review before they can be merged into the main codebase. This typically involves one or more engineers reviewing the code for correctness, readability, efficiency, and adherence to coding standards.\n\n3. **Use of Tools**: Google uses internal tools for code review, such as Critique, which allows developers to comment on specific lines of code, track changes, and manage the review process.\n\n4. **Review Criteria**: Reviewers assess code against various criteria, including functionality, performance, security, and maintainability. They may also consider the impact of changes on existing code.\n\n5. **Feedback and Collaboration**: The review process encourages constructive feedback and collaboration. Reviewers may request changes or improvements, and developers are expected to engage in discussions to resolve any concerns raised.\n\n6. **Approval Process**: Once the code has been reviewed and any necessary changes have been made, reviewers typically approve the changes, allowing the code to be merged.\n\n7. **Documentation and Traceability**: Code reviews involve documenting discussions, decisions, and any agreed-upon changes. This ensures that there is a record of the review process, which can be useful for future reference.\n\n8. **Training and Guidelines**: Google provides guidelines and best practices for conducting code reviews, helping to ensure consistency and quality across teams.\n\n9. **Cultural Emphasis**: Google's culture emphasizes open communication and respect, which reflects in the code review process. Feedback is expected to be delivered respectfully and constructively.\n\n10. **Continuous Improvement**: Google encourages teams to continuously refine their code review processes to adapt to new challenges and enhance productivity.\n\nWhile these principles reflect the general approach to code reviews at Google, specific practices may vary between teams or projects. Overall, code reviews are a critical component of maintaining high-quality software and fostering a collaborative engineering culture.",
